# Build output
/iterion
# contrib helper binaries (built with `go build -o <name> ./contrib/<name>`).
# Source lives under contrib/<name>/; the compiled binary is a build
# artefact, not source — anchored at repo root so it can't shadow the dir.
/mattermost-clarify
*.exe
# Vendored Wails ships the WebView2 bootstrapper as a real .exe under
# vendor/. The global *.exe ignore otherwise hides it from `git add`,
# and Windows desktop builds fail at //go:embed for the missing file.
!vendor/**/*.exe

# Store data
.iterion/
.iterion-*/

# whole_improve_loop (issue #12) persists its package-chunk rotation
# cursor AND its cross-run clean_streak here when dogfooded on this repo.
# It's coverage+convergence state, not source — regenerable (delete to
# restart coverage and the streak from 0).
.whole_improve_loop.state

# Sandbox runtime scratch — the container redirects HOME / XDG_CACHE_HOME
# and the Go toolchain caches (GOPATH / GOCACHE) into the bind-mounted
# worktree (devbox writes its version cache there, `go test`/`go build`
# populate the module + build caches, etc). These are per-run caches,
# never source. Without ignoring them they (a) leak into
# commit-and-finalize's `git add -A` and land in the run's storage
# branch, and (b) explode the studio run-view diff: `git status -uall`
# expands an un-ignored .tmp-gocache into 20k+ entries and the file/diff
# panel renders them all, freezing the UI. The `.tmp-*/` glob catches
# any future per-run scratch dir of this family.
.tmp-*/
# Same family, different name: a sandboxed `go` invocation with a
# workspace-relative GOMODCACHE drops a `.gomodcache/` (module + Go
# toolchain auto-download cache) into the worktree. It slipped past
# `.tmp-*/` once and rode commit-and-finalize's `git add -A` onto a
# storage branch — ignore it explicitly.
.gomodcache/

# Playwright MCP scratch (console logs + page snapshots written under
# cwd by the @playwright/mcp server; per-run, not committed). Also
# catches stray screenshots Playwright drops at the repo root when an
# agent prompt forgets to give it an explicit path.
.playwright-mcp/
/*-screenshot.png
/example-*.png

# IDE
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
node_modules
.pnpm-store
.falcon/
.env
studio/dist/
studio/node_modules/
# This is a pnpm workspace (see pnpm-workspace.yaml). Lockfiles from
# other package managers bypass pnpm-lock.yaml and produce silently
# divergent dependency trees — never commit them.
package-lock.json
**/package-lock.json
yarn.lock
**/yarn.lock
# …except inside e2e fixtures, where the lockfile IS the deliberately-pinned
# test artifact (e.g. renovacy security_audit needs a real npm lockfile to
# scan via osv-scanner --lockfile=).
!e2e/fixtures/**/package-lock.json
!e2e/fixtures/**/yarn.lock
pkg/server/static/assets/
pkg/server/static/index.html
pkg/server/static/*.png
pkg/server/static/*.ico
pkg/server/static/*.json
pkg/server/static/*.xml
!pkg/server/static/.gitkeep

# Dispatcher zero-config bot catalogue — generated by
# `task templates:dispatch-bots` from examples/ + dispatch_bots_default.bot.
# The directory is embedded into the binary at compile time via
# //go:embed in pkg/cli/dispatch_defaults.go but the contents are
# regenerated rather than versioned to avoid duplicating examples/.
pkg/cli/templates/dispatch_bots/*
!pkg/cli/templates/dispatch_bots/.gitkeep

.task/

# Live-test workspace symlinks — created by writeLiveTestReport so
# the user can find recent runs via `ls e2e/.workspaces/`.
e2e/.workspaces/

*.tsbuildinfo

# Local user state (consolidated under .local/)
.local/

# Claude
.claude/*.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# Wails / Iterion Desktop
build/bin/
cmd/iterion-desktop/wailsjs/
cmd/iterion-desktop/frontend-stub/dist/
*.app/
# Build artefacts only — patterns are anchored / scoped so they cannot
# shadow the cmd/iterion-desktop/ source directory itself. An unanchored
# `iterion-desktop` would match the source dir as a path component and
# silently make ~30 .go files invisible to git.
/iterion-desktop
/iterion-desktop-darwin-*
/iterion-desktop-linux-*
/iterion-desktop-windows-*
/build/bin/iterion-desktop
/build/bin/iterion-desktop-*

# Helm chart sub-chart archives — regenerated by `helm dependency
# update`, not source. Keep Chart.yaml's `dependencies:` block as the
# canonical pin; CI / operators run `task chart:lint` to re-fetch.
charts/iterion/charts/
charts/iterion/Chart.lock

# .botz bundles — produced by `iterion bundle pack <dir>`. Source dirs
# (`examples/<bot-name>/{bot.iter,manifest.yaml,...}`) ARE committed;
# the resulting archive is not — it's a deterministic build artefact
# regenerable from source. The default `iterion bundle init` scaffolds
# a per-bundle .gitignore that excludes `*.botz` inside its own dir,
# but that doesn't catch archives written one level up (the common
# layout: source at examples/X/ + archive at examples/X.botz). Anchor
# at the repo root so any *.botz at any depth is excluded.
*.botz
.plans/

# Revi (review-pr) writes its findings markdown to .review-pr/findings.md by
# default (report_path) — a per-run local artifact, not source. Ignore it when
# dogfooding Revi on this repo (or point report_path at /tmp for a dry run).
.review-pr/
